
From "One Pot Paleo" by Jenny Castaneda, pg 37

1 Tbsp tallow (or other oil)
3 cloves garlic, minced
1" ginger, peeled and stripped
1/2 onion
1.5 lbs chicken, cut into bit sized pieces
1 tsp fish sauce
20oz can of chunked pineapple
2c Coconut Milk
1/2 lb mini sweet peppers
1 small head cauliflower, cut into florets

Add oil to pan over medium high heat.
Saute garlic, ginger, and onions until fragrant (~2 minutes)
Add chicken and fish sauce.  Cook until browned.
Lower heat to medium and add pineapple juice.
Simmer 8-10 minutes, until juice reduced by half

Add coconut milk, pineapple chunks, peppers, and
cauliflower.  Simmer ~10 minutes.

Serve hot.
